          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "LINAC"
                ],
                "institute": "1USALAS"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The experiment was performed at flight",
                "path 2 of the Manuel Lujan Neutron Scattering Center.",
                "Neutrons were created via the spallation process:",
                "the 800-MeV pulsed proton beam from the Los Alamos",
                "Neutron Science Center linac was accumulated in a",
                "proton storage ring and then bombarded a tungsten",
                "spallation targe"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The target was an 87.6% enriched 117Sn solid metal",
                "target, in the form of a rectangle of 7.7 cm x 6.3",
                "cm on average and 1.3-cm thick."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CSICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The detector was an array of 24 CsI crystals",
                "placed around the sample, providing approximately",
                "3.0p of detection solid angle, for detection of",
                "gamma rays from neutron capture. These crystals were",
                "packed tightly in a cylindrical array, with a 20-cm",
                "cylindrical hole through the middle to allow access",
                "for the neutron beam and a hollow cylinder of",
                "6Li-loaded polyethylene as a shield."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The neutron energy was determined from the",
                "time-of-flight over a 59-m flight path from source",
                "to CsI detector array."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "SPALL"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The neutron beam produced by spallation of",
                "800 MeV protons in tungsten target was polarized by",
                "transmission through a polarized proton target.The",
                "transmitted neutron beam was approximately 70%",
                "polarized. The polarized protons were produced in",
                "frozen ammonia by dynamic nuclear polarization."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MLA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A multilevel, multichannel formalism of Reich",
                "and Moore was used for the neutron cross sections,",
                "which were convoluted with the TOF resolution function"
              ]
            }
          ],
